= Action name = PCK.AUTOMIC_TENABLE_IO.PUB.ACTION.DOWNLOAD_WEB_APP_SCAN_RESULT
= General Description = This action fetches result of web-app scan which can further be analyzed.
= Failure Conditions = * If Retry Count number reaches to the provided count and result is not fetched.
= Inputs = - Scan ID* :Provide ID of the scan to get its results. E.g. 42 - Chapters : Specify chapters to include in the export in a semi-colon delimited string as combination of the options: vuln_hosts_summary, vuln_by_host, compliance_exec, remediations, vuln_by_plugin, compliance. - Format : Provide UUID for the editor template to use. E.g. csv - File : Provide file name with full path to download. E.g. C:\Automic\Automation.Platform\Agents\rapidautomation\WEBSERVICEREST01\bin\..\temp\log-0001311058.txt - Initial Waiting Time (in min) : Provide initial waiting time. E.g. 5 - Retry Count : Provide the number of retry attempts to get the status.E.g. 10 - Retry Interval (in sec): Provide the interval in seconds between retry attempt.E.g. 120
= Behavior = * Action will fail if user give incorrect path is provided for File field. * If user do not provide any path in File field , A file will be created in WEBSERVICEREST working directory with name log-[Action run id]. * If user only provide the file name then file will created under the WEBSERVICEREST working directory. * If file is already existing with same name, action will overwrite it.
= Implementation Guide = * Action uses 3 jobs for downloading result. First job will prepare a file, second job will check if file is ready to be downloaded and third for which downloads the file. Timeout parameters are used to checking if file is ready to be downloaded or not i.e. Second job in action.
= Return Value = - Log File Path: File path where file is saved.
= Logging = AE logs will be displayed in the AE report.
= Rollback = (none)
= Example = - Scan ID*: 42 - Chapters : vuln_hosts_summary - Format* : csv - File : C:\automic\log-scan-report.csv - Initial Waiting Time (in min) : 5 - Retry Count : 10 - Retry Interval (in sec) : 120
